<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One question that is never worth a=
sking about anything related to cryptocurrency is, =E2=80=9Cis this a joke?=
=E2=80=9D Essentially everything in cryptocurrency is simultaneously seriou=
s and a joke. This is partly explained by the history of crypto=E2=80=94cry=
pto is Extremely Online, and everything Extremely Online is both serious an=
d a joke=E2=80=94but it is also something essential to its nature. If I tol=
d you that there was a vast oil reservoir in my backyard, that would be eit=
her true or not true. Oil is a real physical substance; you can look at it =
and touch it and burn it as fuel. But if I told you I had a vast stash of M=
attcoins, and proposed to give you some for a sandwich or a yacht, we would=
 be on less solid ground. Whether the Mattcoins are a valuable currency exc=
hangeable for sandwiches and yachts, or just a joke I made up, is a social =
fact; it depends on what you think about Mattcoins, and perhaps on whether =
you find them funny. Crypto is a form of collective storytelling; its truth=
 or falsity does not depend on externally verifiable facts in the world but=
 rather on people=E2=80=99s attitudes toward it. It=E2=80=99s a parody if y=
ou think it=E2=80=99s a parody, but if you think it=E2=80=99s real then it=
=E2=80=99s real.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here I want to be a bit speculative, and I als=
o want to write in all caps: NONE OF THIS IS LEGAL ADVICE. But if you have =
a certain sort of mind, you might notice a potential legal arbitrage here. =
The arbitrage is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You intentionally=C2=A0sell people a =
worthless thing, for real money, which you keep.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin=
-bottom: 5px;">If anyone complains =E2=80=94=C2=A0if you get sued or arrest=
ed =E2=80=94=C2=A0then=C2=A0you say you were kidding. (But you keep the mon=
ey, which after all is a crucial element of the joke.)</li>=09<li style=3D"=
margin-bottom: 5px;">You kind of were! And kind of weren=E2=80=99t!=C2=A0</=
li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Again! I am not recommending this as a strateg=
y! I am just observing certain patterns in the world! But for a while durin=
g the initial-coin-offering boom there were a lot of ICOs that <em>explicit=
ly</em> said things like =E2=80=9Cwe are offering a token that is worthless=
, so we can have money,=E2=80=9D and, you know, I hope they had good lawyer=
s.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or take non-fungible tokens. One common approa=
ch with NFTs is that there is some sort of physical or electronic object, a=
nd you sell an NFT =E2=80=9Cof=E2=80=9D it. The relationship between the NF=
T and the object is that the NFT is a label referring to the object. That=
